	(291,'Radek Stepanek vs David Goffin','2012-05-28 14:30:00',83,'Tennis','David Goffin',10,0,0,0,0,0,'','Win,40,-0.34,-4.83,-10.03//','','ebookconverter//Win //\'David Goffin is one of the new, promising youngsters coming through tennis\'s ranks. He\'s already a tournament winner on the Challenger Tour and has been competting with expected youthful excuberance on the main tour as well. He got to the quarter-finals of the ATP Chennai.<br />\n<br />\nThis is a classic case of one on the up facing one on the down. Stepanek has long been one of the tour\'s regular players but he\'s definitely on the decline now and hasn\'t had a serious effect in the majors for couple of years now. It\'s very likely the longer matches are too much for the old boy now, and facing a youngster with talent and all the energy that youth brings could once again be too much for Stepanek.<br />\n<br />\nGoffin is a shade lucky to be here. He actually lost out in qualifying but gets in as a lucky loser. He\'ll be keen to make as much use of that wild-card as possible. <br />\n<br />\nStepanek played in last week\'s Team Cup but only won one match out of four on the clay. He may find himself simply overpowered today.\'@@'),
