	(1563,'Xavier Malisse vs Brian Baker','2012-05-28 15:00:00',83,'Tennis','Xavier Malisse',27,0,0,0,0,0,'','Win,48,-1.45,-3.64,-8.02//','Bobsselections,Win ,151,62.91%,9.02,0.08//maisa,Win ,557,44.34%,26.12,0.09//bestscp,Win ,70,70.00%,6.90,0.17//','ebookconverter//Win //\'Not many people will have heard of Brian Baker before his surge as a wild-card all the way to the final in Nice last week. The world number 216 won seven matches to reach the final, taking care of Davydenko and Monfils along the way, before capitulating rather tamely against Nicolas Almagro in the final.<br />\n<br />\nThat was a hard shift just a wek prior to a grand slam event and I just wonder how much Baker will have left in the tank. He\'s inot five-set territory now and that could tell.<br />\n<br />\nHis opponent, Xavier Malisse was once a Wimbledon semi-finalist but has gradually slipped down the rankings. However he\'s been showing glimpses of a return to form and his attitude in defeat against Joh Isner in Nice last week was positive. Although he went down in straight sets he spurned a number of chances, including a healthy second set tie-break lead where he was only two points away from winning it. But it was his reaction to defeat that I liked. He knew he had thrown it away and slammed the racket into his own foot several times in anger at himself. That could be a sign that Malisse is feeling good about his play right now, and with Baker possibly feeling the effects of his run to the final in Nice, he\'s a top bet here.\'@@'),
